<!-- METHODOLOGY -->
<section class="sec method" id="methodology">
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <p class="ew rv">The Framework</p>
    <h2 class="sec-hl rv">FOUR LAYERS.<br><em>DETERMINISTIC.</em><br>ZERO GUESSWORK.</h2>
    <div class="method-grid">
      <div class="rv">
        <div class="layers">
          <div class="layer"><div class="layer-n">L1</div><div class="layer-c"><div class="layer-t">Firmographic Gate</div><div class="layer-s">Binary pass/fail. Economic viability check. Eliminates 60% of noise before any human touches it.</div></div><div class="layer-badge b-g">Gate</div></div>
          <div class="layer"><div class="layer-n">L2</div><div class="layer-c"><div class="layer-t">Technographic Context</div><div class="layer-s">Stack velocity, not snapshots. Migrations and adoption patterns reveal strategic direction.</div></div><div class="layer-badge b-c">Context</div></div>
          <div class="layer"><div class="layer-n">L3</div><div class="layer-c"><div class="layer-t">Psychographic Signal</div><div class="layer-s">Language mining for buyer state. The most overlooked layer. The highest-converting signal.</div></div><div class="layer-badge b-s">Signal</div></div>
          <div class="layer"><div class="layer-n">L4</div><div class="layer-c"><div class="layer-t">Behavioral Timing</div><div class="layer-s">Trigger events and urgency windows. The narrow moment when a company is actually in market.</div></div><div class="layer-badge b-t">Timing</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="method-right rv d2">
        <div class="m-pullquote">"The framework is deterministic because <em>probabilistic scoring produces probabilistic outcomes.</em> We don't want probable pipeline. We want signal-verified pipeline."</div>
        <div class="m-copy">Most GTM tools collapse these 4 layers into a single lead score. That's the mistake. Each layer answers a fundamentally different question about a company's readiness to buy — and they can't be averaged without <strong>destroying the signal.</strong><br><br>L1 is a gate. L2 is context. L3 is state. L4 is timing. Sequential dependencies, not parallel inputs. Remove any one and your ICP becomes a demographic profile — useful for targeting, useless for timing.</div>
        <a href="assessment.html" class="btn-fire" style="align-self:flex-start;"><span>Assess Your Signal Gaps →</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

